news.title: HC seeks 'specific details' of illegal construction in Aravalis
news.para: The matter is pending before the HC in the wake of a petition seeking directions to ban construction in Aravalli Hills by defining it as a forest area. The matter is pending before the HC since May 2018.

news.title: Stakeholders seek Mysuru civic body to expand tax net during pre-budget meeting
news.para: They put forward many such suggestions during the first pre-budget consultations meeting 2023-24, chaired by Mayor Shivakumar, held at Jayachamarajendra Wadiyar Meeting Hall on MCC office premises in the city.

news.title: Ghaziabad civic body set to bring 2.4 lakh houses under tax ambit
news.para: With this, the cash-strapped municipal body hopes to generate an additional Rs 100 crore by the end of the 2022-23 fiscal.

news.title: Suburbs lack town planning even as Kochi grows eastwards
news.para: Several industries, sports and healthcare facilities, etc, are coming up in Kalamassery area while Kakkanad area is witnessing mushrooming of IT and allied services.

news.title: Why some Noida societies want single-point connections
news.para: Officials said they had identified 55 highrises for the conversion. Of these, they added, 26 were yet to respond to notices on their choice of power connections.

news.title: Can't allow illegal buildings seeking regularisation: Madras HC
news.para: If an unauthorised construction has been put up, it should be ordered to be demolished, thereby sending a strong warning signal to perpetrators of such offences.

news.title: Real estate sharks are selling Chennai's last remaining lakes too
news.para: The locality has tiny houses built in a haphazard manner. No roads, no stormwater drains or underground sewage network.

news.title: HDFC hikes lending rate by 35 bps to 8.65%
news.para: The retail prime lending rate on housing loans, on which the adjustable rate home loans are benchmarked, has been increased by 35 basis points to 8.65 per cent onwards, effective December 20, the bank said in a regulatory filing.

news.title: Edifice Engineering told to clear Supertech twin towers' rubble by January-end
news.para: ​The move comes after the residents’ welfare association (RWA) of the nearby society — Emerald Court — wrote to the authority, alleging delay in clearing the site, which was supposed to be completed by November 28.

news.title: Six years & eight deadlines on, DLF colonies' takeover still stuck in Gurugram
news.para: The developer, DLF, has however claimed that the department of town and country planning (DTCP) is yet to issue a completion certificate for all three areas, without which takeover is not possible.

news.title: About 2,800 projects worth Rs 90,000 crore lapse in five years of Maharashtra RERA
news.para: A high-ranking bureaucrat told TOI that for MahaRera, led by veteran IAS officer Ajoy Mehta, the top priority, and the biggest challenge, would be to revive the lapsed projects in a time-bound manner and ensure that justice is done to home buyers.

news.title: Government to refund GST if purchase of incomplete house called off: Experts
news.para: The finance ministry said in the 48th GST Council meeting that there is no procedure for claim of refund of tax borne by unregistered buyers in cases where the contract or agreement for supply of services, such as construction of flat or house and long-term insurance policy, is cancelled and the time period of issuance of credit note by the concerned supplier is over.

news.title: Now, pollution ratings for building sites in Haryana
news.para: The Haryana pollution control board on Friday released a scoring system through which the sites will be marked. There will be 29 parameters in total and the maximum score will be 220.

news.title: Haryana RERA asks Pareena Laxmi Infra to pay delayed possession charges to 51 allottees
news.para: A group of 51 allottees of Pareena Laxmi had approached RERA demanding delayed possession charges since the builder failed to deliver the units in specified period of four years from execution of the builder-buyer agreement in 2016.

news.title: UP-RERA imposes Rs 1.77 crore penalty on 13 builders over non-compliance of orders
news.para: The RERA during a meeting on Monday reviewed the status of compliance of its orders by the promoters of the realty projects. The authority found that some of the developers have indulged in non-compliance despite being granted sufficient time.
